REESE:

14:32.455 --> 14:33.914
Spread your legs!

14:33.956 --> 14:35.124
MALCOLM:

14:33.956 --> 14:35.124
No!

14:35.166 --> 14:36.376
REESE:

14:35.166 --> 14:36.376
I said spread your legs!

14:36.417 --> 14:37.502
MALCOLM:

14:36.417 --> 14:37.502
No!

14:37.544 --> 14:38.919
It's time for the talk, Hal.

14:38.961 --> 14:40.547
REESE:

14:38.961 --> 14:40.547
Come on, spread your legs!

14:40.588 --> 14:42.841
MALCOLM:

14:40.588 --> 14:42.841
I'm not spreading my legs!

14:47.345 --> 14:48.638
(chanting): Fight, fight, fight!

14:47.345 --> 14:48.638
Fight harder!

14:48.680 --> 14:50.390
Wildcats, help us out, fight!

14:50.431 --> 14:51.850
Fight, fight, fight!

14:51.891 --> 14:52.933
Fight harder!

14:52.975 --> 14:54.853
Wildcats, help us out, fight!

14:54.894 --> 14:58.022
We got spirit!

14:54.894 --> 14:58.022
Wildcats, we got spirit!

14:58.064 --> 15:00.859
Wildcats, we got what?

14:58.064 --> 15:00.859
What, what, what?

15:00.900 --> 15:02.819
What, what, what,

15:00.900 --> 15:02.819
what, what, what, what?

15:02.861 --> 15:03.944
We got spirit!

15:03.986 --> 15:05.946
Wildcats, we got spirit!

15:05.988 --> 15:08.742
Wildcats, we got what?

15:05.988 --> 15:08.742
What, what, what?

15:08.783 --> 15:10.951
What, what, what,

15:08.783 --> 15:10.951
what, what, what, what?

15:10.993 --> 15:12.871
We got spirit!

15:12.912 --> 15:14.539
(cheering)

15:14.581 --> 15:16.583
Yes. Yes.

15:17.291 --> 15:18.334
(sniffs)

15:18.376 --> 15:20.961
Reese, that was incredible.

15:21.003 --> 15:22.963
Who's been helping you

15:21.003 --> 15:22.963
on your spirit kicks?

15:26.509 --> 15:28.177
(laughing)

15:33.015 --> 15:35.976
(Reese sobbing loudly)

15:36.018 --> 15:39.856
Come on, Reese,

15:36.018 --> 15:39.856
I really have to go!

15:39.898 --> 15:43.443
I'm the most worthless,

15:39.898 --> 15:43.443
putrid loser in the world.

15:43.484 --> 15:44.985
Everybody hates me.

15:45.027 --> 15:46.237
I  hate me.

15:46.279 --> 15:47.655
(sobbing)

15:47.697 --> 15:48.989
Your brother in there?

15:49.031 --> 15:50.991
Where else?

15:51.033 --> 15:53.828
Reese? Come on out.

15:51.033 --> 15:53.828
We need to have a talk.

15:53.870 --> 15:54.995
Finally.

15:55.037 --> 15:57.164
No, Malcolm, you're in

15:55.037 --> 15:57.164
on this talk, too.

15:57.206 --> 15:58.666
Me? Why do I

15:57.206 --> 15:58.666
have to be here?

15:58.708 --> 16:00.794
Relax-- it's going to be

15:58.708 --> 16:00.794
far worse for me

16:00.835 --> 16:03.003
than it is for you.

16:03.045 --> 16:04.297
Boys, this talk

16:04.338 --> 16:05.882
is very important,

16:05.924 --> 16:08.593
so I need

16:05.924 --> 16:08.593
your undivided attention.

16:08.635 --> 16:10.010
It's very important

16:10.052 --> 16:12.054
that you be bored

16:10.052 --> 16:12.054
and squirm a lot.

16:12.096 --> 16:14.265
Now, I want to tell you

16:12.096 --> 16:14.265
about what happens

16:14.307 --> 16:17.017
when a boy really,

16:14.307 --> 16:17.017
really likes a girl.

16:17.059 --> 16:20.647
And, Dewey, I'll try to make

16:17.059 --> 16:20.647
this easy for you to understand.

16:20.688 --> 16:22.022
Ah.

16:23.274 --> 16:26.026
Aw, man, I still

16:23.274 --> 16:26.026
play with that.

16:26.068 --> 16:27.487
Here we go.

16:27.528 --> 16:29.405
You see, there's a certain thing

16:27.528 --> 16:29.405
that happens

16:29.447 --> 16:31.031
between normal, healthy people.

16:31.073 --> 16:33.326
It's called chemistry.

16:33.367 --> 16:34.869
Well, that doesn't happen.

16:34.911 --> 16:36.287
Except maybe the first time.

16:36.329 --> 16:37.747
What  does  happen

16:37.789 --> 16:38.832
is this.

16:38.873 --> 16:40.291
I like you.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.042
(high-pitched voice):

16:40.333 --> 16:42.042
I like you, too.

16:42.084 --> 16:43.670
And if they love each other

16:43.711 --> 16:45.421
and take the proper precautions,

16:43.711 --> 16:45.421
they'll have sex.

16:45.463 --> 16:47.131
But I've told you

16:45.463 --> 16:47.131
about that already.

16:47.173 --> 16:48.048
Not me.

16:48.090 --> 16:50.259
Well, ask your brothers.

16:51.761 --> 16:55.055
Now, unfortunately,

16:51.761 --> 16:55.055
if the boy is from our family,

16:55.097 --> 16:57.934
it goes a little more like this.

16:57.976 --> 16:59.059
I like you.

16:59.101 --> 17:00.561
I hate you!

17:00.603 --> 17:02.856
Now I love you!

17:02.897 --> 17:04.064
Leave me alone!

17:04.106 --> 17:05.984
Your insane neediness

17:04.106 --> 17:05.984
is driving me away!

17:06.025 --> 17:08.068
Look at me! Look at me!

17:08.110 --> 17:09.278
Look, oh, I'm crazy! Look-it!

17:09.320 --> 17:10.864
Ooh! Ooh! Pay attention to me!

17:10.905 --> 17:12.699
Look at me!

17:10.905 --> 17:12.699
Look at me! I'm crazy!

17:12.740 --> 17:14.074
I'm an idiot!

17:14.116 --> 17:15.075
Watch me crash and burn!

17:15.117 --> 17:16.786
(hooting)

17:16.828 --> 17:18.955
There's no explaining it.

17:18.997 --> 17:20.247
It's hereditary.

17:20.289 --> 17:22.082
And it goes back

17:20.289 --> 17:22.082
for generations.

17:22.124 --> 17:24.669
Francis has it,

17:22.124 --> 17:24.669
so does Uncle Pete.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.546
It's why your great

17:24.711 --> 17:26.546
grandpa went to work

17:26.587 --> 17:27.922
on that oil rig in Peru.

17:27.964 --> 17:30.132
All I know is

17:27.964 --> 17:30.132
your mother must carry

17:30.174 --> 17:31.968
some sort of internal antidote,

17:32.010 --> 17:36.055
because, through some fluke,

17:32.010 --> 17:36.055
I was lucky enough to get her.

17:37.598 --> 17:40.018
I just wanted you boys

17:37.598 --> 17:40.018
to know what you were in for.

17:45.189 --> 17:49.027
There was so much I

17:45.189 --> 17:49.027
wanted to tell her...

17:49.068 --> 17:51.111
but she was gone.

17:51.153 --> 17:54.407
And I... I...

17:54.448 --> 17:55.783
Come on, sir.

17:55.825 --> 17:57.117
Just say it.

17:57.159 --> 17:59.704
I hated her!

17:59.746 --> 18:01.956
(sobbing)

18:06.002 --> 18:08.212
(sniffles)

18:08.254 --> 18:11.131
All these issues with my mother.

18:11.173 --> 18:14.802
I know now that this

18:11.173 --> 18:14.802
was not an accident.

18:16.596 --> 18:18.973
You know, talking with you

18:16.596 --> 18:18.973
has helped me

18:19.015 --> 18:21.434
work out some things

18:19.015 --> 18:21.434
with my own family.

18:22.810 --> 18:24.437
I mean, all those years

18:22.810 --> 18:24.437
I blamed my parents

18:24.478 --> 18:28.148
for every senseless act

18:24.478 --> 18:28.148
of self-destruction.

18:28.190 --> 18:31.193
And all this time, I was

18:28.190 --> 18:31.193
at least partially responsible

18:31.235 --> 18:33.112
for a couple of them.

18:34.196 --> 18:36.240
(school bell ringing)

18:49.670 --> 18:51.422
You know, it really

18:49.670 --> 18:51.422
means a lot to me

18:51.464 --> 18:54.174
to know that I can come to you

18:51.464 --> 18:54.174
when I need to talk.

18:54.216 --> 18:56.469
Familiarity

18:54.216 --> 18:56.469
breeds contempt, Cadet.

19:08.188 --> 19:09.189
What are you doing?

19:09.231 --> 19:10.357
What's the point?

19:10.399 --> 19:12.568
You heard Dad. I'm doomed!

19:12.610 --> 19:15.237
You can't quit! I've worked

19:12.610 --> 19:15.237
too hard for you to quit now!

19:15.279 --> 19:16.823
I hate to inform you, brain boy,

19:16.864 --> 19:18.658
it's not about you,

19:16.864 --> 19:18.658
it's about me.

19:18.699 --> 19:20.576
That's before I spent

19:18.699 --> 19:20.576
an entire day

19:20.618 --> 19:22.078
with your hand on my ass!

19:22.120 --> 19:23.203
You owe me!

19:23.245 --> 19:24.204
I can't help you.

19:24.246 --> 19:25.665
Yes, you can!

19:25.706 --> 19:28.208
You can break the cycle

19:25.706 --> 19:28.208
Dad was talking about!

19:28.250 --> 19:29.919
You have to talk to Wendy!

19:29.961 --> 19:31.587
I can't! I freeze up!

19:31.629 --> 19:34.715
Do you want to end up

19:31.629 --> 19:34.715
like Francis? Or Uncle Pete?

19:34.757 --> 19:35.925
I don't care anymore!

19:35.967 --> 19:37.426
Anything's better than this!

19:37.468 --> 19:40.346
Even marrying Mom?

19:43.265 --> 19:47.227
Dewey, your mother and I

19:43.265 --> 19:47.227
want to talk to you.

19:47.269 --> 19:49.105
You're a good boy.

19:49.147 --> 19:50.272
But in life,

19:50.314 --> 19:51.273
being good doesn't always

19:51.315 --> 19:53.067
get you the things you want.

19:54.276 --> 19:55.736
I guess what I'm trying

19:54.276 --> 19:55.736
to say is

19:55.778 --> 19:58.156
that when your mother and I

19:55.778 --> 19:58.156
don't buy you a toy,

19:58.197 --> 20:00.074
it doesn't mean

19:58.197 --> 20:00.074
that we don't love you.

20:00.116 --> 20:01.325
Hmm?

20:01.367 --> 20:03.327
You just have to learn

20:01.367 --> 20:03.327
that disappointment

20:03.369 --> 20:05.245
is all part of being a grown-up.

20:05.287 --> 20:08.708
But, luckily,

20:05.287 --> 20:08.708
you're not a grown-up yet!

20:08.749 --> 20:09.876
Ta-da!

20:09.917 --> 20:11.544
Wow!

20:11.585 --> 20:13.838
(both laugh)

20:13.880 --> 20:16.549
Oh, come on,

20:13.880 --> 20:16.549
how cute is that?

20:18.092 --> 20:19.426
Break me.

20:19.468 --> 20:20.594
Okay.

20:21.345 --> 20:23.181
(chuckles)

20:23.222 --> 20:25.933
Okay, second row.

20:27.601 --> 20:29.896
Okay, ready?

20:27.601 --> 20:29.896
Here we go.

20:31.772 --> 20:34.274
I... I...

20:34.316 --> 20:36.652
Did you say something?

20:36.694 --> 20:38.988
Wendy, I really like you.

20:39.030 --> 20:41.365
Like when a boy likes a girl--

20:39.030 --> 20:41.365
normal and healthy.

20:41.407 --> 20:43.910
I'm sorry for hurting

20:41.407 --> 20:43.910
you all those times.

20:43.951 --> 20:45.327
I'm really

20:43.951 --> 20:45.327
not a bad guy.

20:45.369 --> 20:49.248
Anyways... thanks.

20:52.210 --> 20:54.170
I like you, too.

20:56.047 --> 20:57.548
Really?

20:57.590 --> 20:58.966
Yeah.

20:59.008 --> 21:01.594
I even kind of liked

20:59.008 --> 21:01.594
your bad boy side, too.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.978
(all screaming)

21:11.020 --> 21:12.688
(gasping)

21:12.730 --> 21:14.607
Oh, my God!

21:14.648 --> 21:16.901
Call...

21:16.943 --> 21:19.486
nine...

21:19.528 --> 21:22.240
one...

21:22.281 --> 21:24.283
(clamoring)

21:28.996 --> 21:31.331
Hello, Mother?

21:31.373 --> 21:33.500
It's Edwin.

21:33.542 --> 21:36.545
Yes, it has been a long time.

21:36.587 --> 21:38.005
So be sure to try

21:38.047 --> 21:40.216
the new and improved

21:38.047 --> 21:40.216
Chip-A-Roo cookie today.

21:40.258 --> 21:43.761
I can make you taller,

21:40.258 --> 21:43.761
I can make you better-looking.

21:43.803 --> 21:47.014
If you eat enough of me,

21:43.803 --> 21:47.014
I can make you president,

21:47.848 --> 21:49.642
maybe even emperor of the world.

21:50.977 --> 21:52.352
Honey, can you buy me

21:50.977 --> 21:52.352
a box of these cookies?

21:52.979 --> 21:54.063
Make it two.

21:54.605 --> 21:55.648
Make it two boxes.
